<p>Create a git project and clone it into local</p>

<pre class="prettyprint linenums lang-php">
git clone https://github.com/sambhuRajSingh/DataStructure.git
</pre>

<p>Create Composer.json File with phpunit as its dependencies to be installed</p>

<pre class="prettyprint linenums lang-php">
{
    "name": "Project/DataStructure",
    "require-dev": {
        "phpunit/phpunit": "~4.0"
    },
    "autoload": {
        "psr-4": {
            "DataStructure\\": "app/"
        }
    }
}
</pre>

<p>On terminal run <code>composer install</code></p>

<p>In case, you change psr-4 application name, you will need to run <code>composer dump-autoload -o</code></p>

<p>As you have specified DataSerialisation to be the app folder in the composer file, make
<code>app</code> folder as well as test folder for unit testing</p>

<p>Also create <code>phpunit.xml<code> file. Within it use boilerplate code below and specify
test directory created in earlier step</p>

<pre class="prettyprint linenums lang-php">
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<phpunit colors="true">
    <testsuites>
        <testsuite name="Application Test Suite">
            <directory>./test/</directory>
        </testsuite>
    </testsuites>
</phpunit>

<p class="small">Now, running <code>phpunit</code> on terminal should run all the test inside the test folder</p>
</p>